# LinkWave Wireless - Web Development Rules

## Project Overview
This is a multi-page HTML website for LinkWave Wireless, a wireless network consulting company. The project uses vanilla HTML, CSS, and JavaScript with external libraries (Swiper, Font Awesome, Google Fonts).

## Code Style & Standards

### HTML
- Use semantic HTML5 elements (header, nav, section, article, footer, etc.)
- Always include proper meta tags (charset, viewport)
- Use descriptive alt text for all images
- Maintain consistent indentation (spaces, not tabs)
- Keep HTML structure clean and well-organized
- Use meaningful class and ID names following BEM or similar naming conventions
- Ensure all links have proper href attributes
- Include lang attribute on html tag

### CSS
- Follow consistent naming conventions (use existing patterns in style.css)
- Use CSS custom properties (variables) for colors, spacing, and other repeated values
- Write mobile-first responsive CSS
- Use flexbox and grid appropriately
- Keep styles organized by component/section
- Avoid inline styles unless absolutely necessary
- Use meaningful class names that describe purpose, not appearance
- Ensure proper vendor prefixes when needed
- Avoid !important overrides until absolutely necessary

### JavaScript
- Use modern ES6+ syntax
- Write clean, readable code with meaningful variable names
- Add comments for complex logic
- Handle errors appropriately
- Keep functions small and focused on single responsibilities
- Use const/let appropriately (avoid var)

## Project Structure
- HTML files are in the root directory
- Images are organized in folders by page/section (e.g., index_images/, our_services_images/)
- Shared CSS is in style.css
- Shared JavaScript is in script.js
- Maintain consistent file naming (lowercase with underscores)

## Design & UX Guidelines
